%N A396820 Decimal expansion of (479 - 52*sqrt(2))/576.
%C A396820 The probability that the convex hull of four points independently and uniformly selected at random in the interior of a regular octagon is a quadrilateral.
%C A396820 Deltheil (1919, 1926) calculated the wrong value (2851 + 2013*sqrt(2))/(4032 + 2880*sqrt(2)) = 0.7030... .
%C A396820 Kendall and Moran (1963) cited this result, and Solomon (1978) gave the wrong complementary probability based on this result (although he also gave the correct general formula based on Alikoski's paper), a value that is cited by Gelca and Andreescu (2017).
%D A396820 H. A. Alikoski, Über das Sylvestersche Vierpunktproblem, Ann. Acad. Sci. Fenn., Vol. 51, No. 7 (1939), pp. 1-10.
%D A396820 Răzvan Gelca and Titu Andreescu, Putnam and Beyond, 2nd ed., Springer, 2017, p. 843.
%H A396820 Robert Deltheil, <a href="https://doi.org/10.5802/afst.311">Sur la théorie des probabilités géométriques</a>, Annales de la faculté des sciences de Toulouse, 3rd series, Vol. 11 (1919), pp. 1-65. See p. 56.
%H A396820 Robert Deltheil, <a href="https://archive.org/details/probabilitesgeom0002rdel/page/54/mode/1up">Probabilités Géométriques</a>, Gauthier-Villars, Paris, 1926, p. 54.
%H A396820 Maurice G. Kendall and P. A. P. Moran, <a href="https://archive.org/details/geometricalproba033077mbp/page/n49/mode/1up">Geometrical Probability</a>, Charles Griffin and Co. Ltd., 1963, p. 46.
%H A396820 Herbert Solomon, <a href="https://archive.org/details/GeometricProbability/page/114/mode/1up">Geometric Probability</a>, Philadelphia: Society for Industrial and Applied Mathematics, 1978, p. 114.
%H A396820 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="http://mathworld.wolfram.com/SylvestersFour-PointProblem.html">Sylvester's Four-Point Problem</a>.
%H A396820 <a href="/index/Al#algebraic_02">Index entries for algebraic numbers, degree 2</a>.
%F A396820 Equals 1 - 4*A396661.
%F A396820 Equals 1 - (9*cos(w)^2 + 52*cos(w) + 44)/(9*n^2*sin(w)^2) with w = 2*Pi/n and n = 8 (Alikoski's general formula for a regular n-gon).
%F A396820 Equals (2833 + 2031*sqrt(2))/(4032 + 2880*sqrt(2)).
%F A396820 Minimal polynomial: 331776*x^2 - 551808*x + 224033.
%e A396820 0.703925164507984474760958656842180034573571289028469...
%t A396820 RealDigits[(479 - 52*Sqrt[2])/576, 10, 120][[1]]
%o A396820 (PARI) (479 - 52*sqrt(2))/576
%Y A396820 Cf. A051050, A051051, A242780 (disk), A394805, A396661, A396819 (regular pentagon), A396821 (regular 10-gon).
